---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Resources - PM Learning Tool"
  description="PM courses, blogs, and reading materials"
>
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Resources</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
        PM courses, blogs, and reading materials
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Recommended PM Courses</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 pl-2">
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.coursera.org/specializations/product-management"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >Product Management Specialization - Coursera</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.udemy.com/course/productmanagement/"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >Product Management Fundamentals - Udemy</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/learning/product-management-foundations"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >Product Management Foundations - LinkedIn Learning</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.productschool.com/"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >Product School Courses</a
          >
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Suggested Blogs and Reading</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 pl-2">
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.svpg.com/articles"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >SVPG - Silicon Valley Product Group</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.mindtheproduct.com/"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal">Mind the Product</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.productplan.com/blog/"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal">ProductPlan Blog</a
          >
        </li>
         <li>
           <a
             href="https://www.romanpichler.com/blog/"
             class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
             >Roman Pichler's Product Management Blog</a
           >
         </li>
         <li>
           <a
             href="https://www.ycombinator.com/library/59-how-to-set-up-hire-and-scale-a-growth-strategy-and-team"
             class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
             >How to set up, hire, and scale a growth strategy and team</a
           >
          </li>
          <li>
            <a
            href="https://blackboxofpm.com/"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >The Black Box of Product Management</a
          >
        </li>
        <li class="mb-4 font-semibold">
          Find, Vet and Close the Best Product Managers - First Round Review<br
          />
          <a
            href="https://review.firstround.com/find-vet-and-close-the-best-product-managers-heres-how/"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >https://review.firstround.com/find-vet-and-close-the-best-product-managers-heres-how/</a
          >
        </li>
        <li class="mb-4 font-semibold">
          Product Manager Archetype - NN/G<br />
          <a
            href="https://www.nngroup.com/articles/product-manager-archetype/"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >https://www.nngroup.com/articles/product-manager-archetype/</a
          >
        </li>
        <li class="mb-4 font-semibold">
          The Product Triad: Design's Role - NN/G<br />
          <a
            href="https://www.nngroup.com/articles/the-product-triad-designs-role/"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >https://www.nngroup.com/articles/the-product-triad-designs-role/</a
          >
        </li>
        <li class="mb-4 font-semibold">
          “Sweat the Details” and Other Commandments for Mapping Out a Career in
          Product<br />
          <a
            href="https://review.firstround.com/sweat-the-details-and-other-commandments-for-mapping-out-a-career-in-product/"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >https://review.firstround.com/sweat-the-details-and-other-commandments-for-mapping-out-a-career-in-product/</a
          >
        </li>
        <li class="mb-4 font-semibold">
          17 Product Managers Who Will Own the Future of NYC Tech — and the 9
          Frameworks They'll Use to Do It<br />
          <a
            href="https://review.firstround.com/17-product-managers-who-will-own-the-future-of-nyc-tech-and-the-9-frameworks-theyll-use-to-do-it/"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >https://review.firstround.com/17-product-managers-who-will-own-the-future-of-nyc-tech-and-the-9-frameworks-theyll-use-to-do-it/</a
          >
        </li>
        <li class="mb-4 font-semibold">
          To Build Great Products, Build This Strong, Scalable System First -
          First Round Review<br />
          <a
            href="https://review.firstround.com/to-build-great-products-build-this-strong-scalable-system-first/"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >https://review.firstround.com/to-build-great-products-build-this-strong-scalable-system-first/</a
          >
        </li>
        <li class="mb-4 font-semibold">
          Why Chefs and Soldiers Make the Best Product Managers - First Round
          Review<br />
          <a
            href="https://review.firstround.com/why-soldiers-and-chefs-make-the-best-product-managers/"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >https://review.firstround.com/why-soldiers-and-chefs-make-the-best-product-managers/</a
          >
        </li>
        <li class="mb-4 font-semibold">
          Analytics for startups : YC Startup Library | Y Combinator<br />
          <a
            href="https://www.ycombinator.com/library/8H-analytics-for-startups"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >https://www.ycombinator.com/library/8H-analytics-for-startups</a
          >
        </li>
        <li class="mb-4 font-semibold">
          How to set up, hire, and scale a growth strategy and team : YC Startup
          Library<br />
          <a
            href="https://www.ycombinator.com/library/59-how-to-set-up-hire-and-scale-a-growth-strategy-and-team"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >https://www.ycombinator.com/library/59-how-to-set-up-hire-and-scale-a-growth-strategy-and-team</a
          >
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Books</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 pl-2">
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.amazon.com/Inspired-Product-Management-Second/dp/1119387507"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >Inspired: How to Create Tech Products Customers Love - Marty Cagan</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.amazon.com/Decode-Agile-Management-Engineers-Leading/dp/1732265186"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >Decode and Conquer: Answers to Product Management Interviews -
            Lewis Lin</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.amazon.com/Practical-Product-Management-Transform-Productivity/dp/1491927336"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >The Practical Product Manager - Robert Siegel</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.amazon.com/Design-Everyday-Things-Donald-Norman/dp/1452637404"
            class="text-accent hover:underline font-normal"
            >The Design of Everyday Things - Don Norman</a
          >
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
